      "raw_text": "/ The carpenters supported Mr.. Good\nais views that too much publicity\nhad been given the millworkers'\nstrike and decided to keep all efforts\ntoward q settlement as secret as DOS\nsible. The chamber Of commerce\ncommittee decided upon the same\ncourse.\n\n\nThe carpenters were appealed to\nbecause they are controlled by the\nsame body as the millworkers and\nmust support any course decided\nupon for the strike by that controll-\nIng body.\n\n\nThey are therefore indirectly in\nterested and their concurrence in any\nplan would have great influence in\nsecuring settlement."
